Of those polled, 79% voted in favour of divorce, while 80% thought marriage should be available to same-sex couples.

The poll on abortion was conducted among more than 950 people and involved interviewers recording personal information on respondents’ attitudes, including age, height, weight, political beliefs and whether they are catholic or not.
